A vintage 1970s computer terminal aesthetic showing a fragmented hard drive platter viewed from above, with scattered geometric data blocks in muted oranges, browns, and cream colors slowly reorganizing themselves into neat concentric circles. The scene is bathed in warm cathode-ray glow, with a small penguin figurine sitting beside the platter, watching the defragmentation process unfold. Dust particles float in the amber light, and the background features wood-grain paneling typical of retro computing spaces. The composition emphasizes the satisfying transformation from chaos to order, with some blocks mid-flight between their old and new positions.
